253
00:15:18,800 --> 00:15:20,320
Now you're with her.

254
00:15:20,920 --> 00:15:21,960
The deeper your feelings for her,

255
00:15:22,120 --> 00:15:23,280
the stronger the poison becomes

256
00:15:23,560 --> 00:15:26,040
and the more painful it will be
when it flares up.

257
00:15:27,120 --> 00:15:27,920
Absurd.

258
00:15:32,400 --> 00:15:33,240
Will I die?

259
00:15:35,240 --> 00:15:36,720
If you keep indulging like this,

260
00:15:37,440 --> 00:15:39,440
it'll eventually flare up big time.

261
00:15:40,800 --> 00:15:41,600
At that point,

262
00:15:42,000 --> 00:15:43,520
there'll be no cure.

263
00:15:47,840 --> 00:15:48,880
Whether you live or die

264
00:15:50,680 --> 00:15:51,960
is up to you.

265
00:15:57,480 --> 00:15:58,400
Don't tell her yet.

266
00:16:07,720 --> 00:16:09,320
That jerk Na Jinci

267
00:16:09,680 --> 00:16:11,320
dared to break
into the Crown Prince Mansion

268
00:16:13,120 --> 00:16:14,560
and seriously injured you!

269
00:16:18,040 --> 00:16:18,800
No way.

270
00:16:19,000 --> 00:16:20,160
I must go to His Majesty

271
00:16:20,480 --> 00:16:22,280
and destroy the Preceptor Mansion.

272
00:16:22,320 --> 00:16:23,120
Stop.

273
00:16:23,960 --> 00:16:25,320
We kidnapped Miss Xie first.

274
00:16:25,680 --> 00:16:27,120
This must not be made public.

275
00:16:27,760 --> 00:16:28,560
But

276
00:16:28,720 --> 00:16:30,600
how can you endure
such humiliation in silence?

277
00:16:32,000 --> 00:16:33,720
I can't swallow this indignation!

278
00:16:36,800 --> 00:16:38,760
Now that Miss Xie has returned,

279
00:16:39,400 --> 00:16:40,760
if she remembers everything,

280
00:16:42,120 --> 00:16:44,000
won't we breed calamities
for the future?

281
00:16:44,200 --> 00:16:45,440
So what if she remembers everything?

282
00:16:46,000 --> 00:16:47,120
She has no proof.

283
00:16:48,040 --> 00:16:49,080
Would the Xie family dare lead troops

284
00:16:49,080 --> 00:16:49,920
against us?

285
00:16:51,640 --> 00:16:53,000
But your father...

286
00:16:53,160 --> 00:16:54,600
The most pressing matter is my father.

287
00:17:01,320 --> 00:17:02,120
Mother.

288
00:17:12,040 --> 00:17:13,360
Are we really afraid

289
00:17:15,520 --> 00:17:17,480
merely of Na Jinci?

290
00:17:19,640 --> 00:17:22,000
What we truly fear is my father

291
00:17:22,960 --> 00:17:24,120
and the imperial power.

292
00:17:37,240 --> 00:17:38,040
Mother,

293
00:17:42,440 --> 00:17:44,200
if I ascend the throne,

294
00:17:48,800 --> 00:17:50,680
be it Na Jinci,

295
00:17:51,160 --> 00:17:53,440
Xie Wanyin or Jiang Mingyue,

296
00:17:54,120 --> 00:17:58,080
all of your worries will be gone.

297
00:18:26,240 --> 00:18:28,430
♪The wind under the eaves♪

298
00:18:28,900 --> 00:18:31,540
♪Gently taps on the wooden door♪

299
00:18:33,290 --> 00:18:35,770
♪The candle flame flickers
as I sleep soundly♪

300
00:18:36,070 --> 00:18:38,450
♪The night is at its peak♪

301
00:18:40,310 --> 00:18:42,560
♪A thunderclap rolls♪

302
00:18:43,030 --> 00:18:45,490
♪Stirring up old dreams again♪

303
00:18:47,630 --> 00:18:49,990
♪Thoughts linger
on the warmth of the past♪

304
00:18:50,180 --> 00:18:53,420
♪The sincerity of the past♪

305
00:18:53,610 --> 00:18:56,770
♪Fireworks fall like rain♪

306
00:18:57,040 --> 00:19:00,040
♪But soon they cool♪

307
00:19:00,590 --> 00:19:04,280
♪I watch as you pass by♪

308
00:19:04,300 --> 00:19:07,390
♪Not daring to ask♪

309
00:19:07,920 --> 00:19:11,210
♪Like the moon, waxing and waning♪

310
00:19:11,210 --> 00:19:14,280
♪How could it ask more?♪

311
00:19:14,550 --> 00:19:19,470
♪You and I are like a small boat
on the river♪

312
00:19:19,730 --> 00:19:24,480
♪Rising and falling with the waves♪

313
00:19:47,390 --> 00:19:49,930
♪Speaking of love and hate♪

314
00:19:50,270 --> 00:19:52,760
♪How can I distinguish them?♪

315
00:19:54,660 --> 00:19:57,050
♪Longing for fate, praying sincerely♪

316
00:19:57,350 --> 00:20:00,400
♪Yet the world does not acknowledge it♪

317
00:20:01,460 --> 00:20:03,820
♪The night grows deep♪

318
00:20:04,230 --> 00:20:07,060
♪Old dreams are stirred again♪

319
00:20:08,830 --> 00:20:11,270
♪Yet the previous ones
are still within them♪

320
00:20:11,460 --> 00:20:14,530
♪Why do they remain silent?♪

321
00:20:14,850 --> 00:20:17,950
♪Fireworks fall like rain♪

322
00:20:18,330 --> 00:20:21,360
♪But soon they cool♪

323
00:20:21,830 --> 00:20:25,540
♪I look, adding a few more strokes
to the word "love"♪

324
00:20:25,710 --> 00:20:28,680
♪A new year's ring♪

325
00:20:29,000 --> 00:20:32,310
♪The cicada's cry is close,
autumn leaves are near♪

326
00:20:32,530 --> 00:20:35,480
♪Yet it's hard to recognize each other♪

327
00:20:36,100 --> 00:20:40,690
♪I sigh, why are you and I♪

328
00:20:41,260 --> 00:20:45,800
♪Rising and falling,
drifting in this way?♪
